sio...\n  Line 52: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775867191750,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79eee199001EOqYActzrfoiz4\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79eed529001jfA3mZTpz8F25b\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2861243a2ffe2hS31hQs5CzQtz\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-b8b1b01a498b4f0b80aefef0f1465a41\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md\",\"limit\":100},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-021 Delta Specification: CLI build 命令\\n2: \\n3: ## Purpose\\n4: \\n5: Implement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces, supporting local Docker builds and cloud provider builds with proxy support, version management, and comprehensive error handling.\\n6: \\n7: ## Requirements\\n8: \\n9: ### Requirement: Build command registration and default options\\n10: \\n11: The system SHALL provide a `build` command that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces with configurable options.\\n12: \\n13: **Acceptance Criteria:**\\n14: - Command name: `build`\\n15: - Supports workspace path specification\\n16: - Supports proxy configuration for dependency resolution\\n17: - Supports cloud provider selection\\n18: - Supports custom output path for build artifacts\\n19: - Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\\n20: \\n21: **Scenarios:**\\n22: \\n23: #### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\\n24: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\\n25: - **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube build` without options\\n26: - **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\\n27:   - `workspace`: `\\\".\\\"` (current directory)\\n28:   - `proxy`: `None`\\n29:   - `cloud_provider`: `None`\\n30:   - `output`: `None`\\n31:   - `verbose`: `False`\\...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z_logs/AR-013_ST-3.log:\n  Line 28: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775867069906,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2861567eeffe7OxVP1P7gfHjxK\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79ed0188001cnorcFxixV1F3H\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79eced2f001NKsGvx6LN4UEVI\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2861567eeffe7OxVP1P7gfHjxK\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_functions.read:10\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-006 Design: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\\n2: \\n3: ## Overview\\n4: \\n5: **AR ID:** AR-006  \\n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \\n7: **Language:** Go  \\n8: **Size:** Medium\\n9: \\n10: The Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management component provides comprehensive lifecycle control for sandboxes in the AgentCube system. It handles graceful shutdown, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan management while integrating with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and Sandbox Creation Handler (AR-005).\\n11: \\n12: The implementation uses the generated client-go library for Kubernetes API interactions with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs, and dynamic client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRD operations.\\n13: \\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: ## Architecture\\n17: \\n18: ### High-Level Design\\n19: \\n20: ```\\n21: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n22: │                       External API Clients                                   │\\n23: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\\n24: │  │  Web UI     │  │   CLI Tool  │  │  Agent SDK  │                         │\\n25: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\\n26: └─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\\n27:           │                │        ...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-026_ST-5.log:\n  Line 7: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866980788,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286147b38ffe4yr2fwmnne0SgF\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79eba60b001GWcv57OUXY4SpS\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79eb9474001C7sDN3qIF0naJT\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286147b38ffe4yr2fwmnne0SgF\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_fa2718c5a1164250bd938147\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-021 — CLI Build Command\\n2: \\n3: - **AR ID**: AR-021\\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\\n5: - **Language**: Python\\n6: - **Size**: M\\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\\n8: \\n9: ## 1. Architecture\\n10: \\n11: ### 1.1 Overview\\n12: \\n13: AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\\n14: \\n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\\n16: \\n17: ```\\n18: cmd/cli/\\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\\n20: ├── agentcube/\\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports app, runtimes\\n22: │   ├── cli/\\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\\n25: │   ├── models/\\n26: │   │   └── pack_models.py                      # MetadataOptions dataclass\\n27: │   ├── runtime/\\n28: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\\n29: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                     # PackRuntime\\n30: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py                    #...\n  Line 8: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866980791,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286147b38ffe4yr2fwmnne0SgF\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79eba204001xx7c0kKf986f00\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79eb9474001C7sDN3qIF0naJT\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286147b38ffe4yr2fwmnne0SgF\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_9b898bbd24c647d9acbf501a\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider\\n2: \\n3: ## Summary\\n4: \\n5: 实现 CLI 的双 Provider 部署能力，支持将 Agent 部署到标准 Kubernetes (Deployment + Service) 或 AgentCube AgentRuntime CRD。\\n6: \\n7: ## Purpose\\n8: \\n9: ### Background\\n10: \\n11: CLI 需要支持多目标部署平台:\\n12: 1. **标准 Kubernetes**: 使用原生 Deployment + Service 资源\\n13: 2. **AgentCube Platform**: 使用 AgentRuntime CRD (自定义资源)\\n14: \\n15: 当前 `KubernetesProvider` 和 `AgentCubeProvider` 已实现基础功能,但与 `cli-toolkit/spec.md` 中的需求存在差距。\\n16: \\n17: ### Goal\\n18: \\n19: 1. 完善 AgentRuntime CRD 部署逻辑,符合规范要求\\n20: 2. 增强 Provider 错误处理和状态检测\\n21: 3. 确保 `publish` 和 `status` 命令正确路由到对应 Provider\\n22: \\n23: ### Value\\n24: \\n25: - **多平台支持**: 同一 CLI 支持 K8s 和 AgentCube 两种部署目标\\n26: - **一致性**: 统一的 Provider 接口抽象\\n27: - **可观