tCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\\n14: \\n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\\n16: \\n17: ```\\n18: cmd/cli/\\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\\n20: ├── agentcube/\\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports app, runtimes\\n22: │   ├── cli/\\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\\n25: │   ├── models/\\n26: │   │   └── pack_models.py                      # MetadataOptions dataclass\\n27: │   ├── runtime/\\n28: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\\n29: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                     # PackRuntime\\n30: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py                    #...\n  Line 20: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866835567,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28617e7d2ffe87RJQv7ZvCA3ub\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79e96dee001Os9Cr7iPrD05AE\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79e94ba6001arDhJElxn5HYCA\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28617e7d2ffe87RJQv7ZvCA3ub\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_0c8e118fd32c4d7682734033\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\",\"offset\":1181},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1181: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\\n1182: \\n1183: ##### Scenario: Global verbose logging\\n1184: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\\n1185: - **WHEN** the callback runs\\n1186: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\\n1187: \\n1188: #### Requirement: `pack` command\\n1189: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\\n1190: \\n1191: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\\n1192: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\\n1193: - **WHEN** options are omitted\\n1194: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\\\".\\\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\\n1195: \\n1196: ##### Scenario: Successful pack\\n1197: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\\n1198...\n  Line 23: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775866847180,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28617e7d2ffe87RJQv7ZvCA3ub\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79e99b65001vj5VcF4acwAXqb\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79e972a5001UA3suj2xLOnVzV\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28617e7d2ffe87RJQv7ZvCA3ub\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_b3813d218cad4d0aa8c826aa\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md\",\"offset\":2472},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n2472: │   └── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\\n2473: └── runtime/\\n2474:     └── pack_runtime.py         # Uses MetadataService\\n2475: ```\\n2476: \\n2477: ## 2. Data Models\\n2478: \\n2479: ### 2.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\\n2480: \\n2481: The core data model representing agent configuration and state.\\n2482: \\n2483: ```python\\n2484: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\\n2485: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\\n2486: \\n2487: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\\n2488:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\\\"Unique name identifying the agent\\\")\\n2489:     description: Optional[str] = None\\n2490:     language: str = \\\"python\\\"\\n2491:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\\\"Command to launch the agent\\\")\\n2492:     port: int = 8080\\n2493:     build_mode: str = \\\"local\\\"\\n2494:     region: Optional[str] = None\\n2495:     version: Optional[str] = None\\n2496:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\\n2497:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\\n2498:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \\\"requirements.txt\\\"\\n2499:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \\\"\\\"\\n2500:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \\\"\\\"\\n2501:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \\\"\\\"\\n2502:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\\n2503:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\\n2504:     router_url: Opti...\n  Line 26: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775866857605,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28617e7d2ffe87RJQv7ZvCA3ub\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79e9b9be001dggRxqNOw2tQZ8\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79e99fff00166pYDeEEWDB4dG\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28617e7d2ffe87RJQv7ZvCA3ub\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The `design.md` file already contains comprehensive technical implementation details for the AgentCube project. It includes:\\n\\n1. **AR-021** - CLI Build Command (complete design)\\n2. **AR-019** - CLI Binary Entry Points (4 binaries: agentd, picod, router, workload-manager)\\n3. **AR-022** - CLI Publish Command (specifications)